Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love and hate are brought together...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.81,0:00:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through both reasoning and suspense!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, we're trapped in the forest with a murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.36,0:00:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's searching for Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.99,0:00:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.82,0:00:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.21,0:01:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.62,0:01:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,e became worried about Mitsuhiko, who skipped out on our morning radio exercising.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.09,0:01:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we all paid a visit to his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.51,0:01:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Mitsuhiko's sister, he told her he was going camping with everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.55,0:02:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But packed only sasa-dango and sunscreen in a backpack and went elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking this was unusual for him, we asked around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.94,0:02:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found out he was in a forest in the Gunma Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.53,0:02:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no matter how many times we tried calling him, Mitsuhiko wouldn't answer his Detective Badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were looking for him, we ran into Officer Yamamura from the Gunma Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.79,0:02:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't want him to hear me say this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one of the elder officers wasn't paying attention, and let him escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.09,0:02:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer, Numabuchi Kiichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.01,0:02:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.76,0:02:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guy I met in Osaka is in this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.68,0:02:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to hurry and leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.72,0:02:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in this forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.23,0:02:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.90,0:02:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry and tell Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} about this, or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Why aren't you answering, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.61,0:02:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beeping again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others came to look for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I answer the badge now, this whole trip would become a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.68,0:03:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko's Mystifying Forest:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.48,0:03:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.65,0:03:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} still won't answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he's just taking a nap somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a chance that Numabuchi Kiichiro has already killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.99,0:03:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't it possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he committed three murders in the Toho, Kanto, and Kinku Prefectures in three consecutive days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.51,0:03:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure know a lot about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.18,0:04:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a big article about it in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the headlines exclaimed...\N"The Serial Killer Who Murdered Three People!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he said when we were interrogating him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He buried his fourth victim in this forest, since his mother was born and raised in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.15,0:04:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he was brought here from Osaka. We'd been searching for the buried corpse all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.20,0:04:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Numabuchi couldn't remember the exact spot, and we couldn't find the body, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.37,0:04:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our colleagues from Osaka left Numabuchi to Senpai and I, but when I left for a minute to get some lunch...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when he ran away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably planning to run away from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.97,0:04:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he didn't seem like the type of person who'd do that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:50.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told us how he used to play by himself in this forest, when his mother came to visit her old home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.98,0:04:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.03,0:04:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I just got a little scratch on my knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.91,0:05:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine, you'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.91,0:05:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The water in this stream is very clean. I even drank from it when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.45,0:05:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, I used to come here to play with my friends all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.17,0:05:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being here with Numabuchi made me feel like I was doing that all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.46,0:05:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this guy's lack of focus, it's no wonder he got away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is sure is troubling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.34,0:05:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't have a clue where that boy is, so how are we supposed to find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.35,0:05:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we've got a few clues, but I don't know if they will help...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three clues, actually!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scent of lemons...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Warlords' names...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.23,0:05:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And sasa-dango!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are those supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got yelled at by some older men for saying the names of two ancient warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.66,0:05:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He packed sasa-dango in his backpack before he came here, and we were told he smelled very strongly of lemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makes no sense to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I know why he smelled like lemons, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.83,0:05:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was most likely wearing lemon grass and citronella oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That combination is often used as a homemade insecticide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.21,0:06:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Insecticide?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, bug spray.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.13,0:06:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember what Mitsuhiko's sister said?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko borrowed the sunscreen that she ordered from overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's rare in Japan, but in other countries, they sell sunscreen that contains insect repellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} didn't use it as a sunblock, but as an insect repellent instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.41,0:06:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That basically means that he was planning to come here from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.54,0:06:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the sasa-dango and warlords' names?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.17,0:06:38.75,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Kibi-dango is a Japanese sweet dumpling made with millet, said to provide quick strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.50,0:06:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the story, didn't Momotaro have kibi-dango?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.89,0:06:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-N-Numabuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, you won't get away again
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too dark and he knows this forest better than any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be the ones in danger if we chase him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.77,0:07:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the time being, we need to focus on finding Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.32,0:07:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't sense his presence just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't feel anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.12,0:07:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he was hiding in that tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.38,0:07:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy's just like Saru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.34,0:07:25.96,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Referring to Saru, the monkey from the Japanese children's story, "Sarukani Gassen" (The Tale of Saru and the Crab).
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.84,0:07:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told me he used to jump from tree to tree when he was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Ushiwakamaru, who trained with Tengu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ushiwakamaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor, watch over everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.49,0:07:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm going to get Mitsuhiko right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.20,0:07:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So just wait there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.42,0:08:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.46,0:08:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't walk any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll just give up and contact Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others on the badge...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.68,0:08:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.77,0:08:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here! I'm right here, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.82,0:08:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.32,0:08:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're very similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.04,0:08:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can hear me, answer your Detective Badge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.42,0:08:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This forest is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.38,0:08:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a serial killer on the loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So give up and answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.31,0:08:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn! Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.14,0:09:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm right, he should be somewhere near this stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi already found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're the boy who was with Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.87,0:09:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought Yamamura took you away from this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one of my friends got lost in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.30,0:09:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is where you were, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why didn't you tell me about the lost child?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.35,0:09:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, I was trying to find the right time to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.48,0:09:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Senpai, I have some great news!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.48,0:09:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found Numabuchi Kiichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:48.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.74,0:09:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You caught him, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.03,0:09:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not! How could I have done that all on my own?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.57,0:09:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I lost track of him in an instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? Where was he hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.42,0:10:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was sitting in a tree just like Saru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. When our eyes met, he jumped down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.01,0:10:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he ran away in the opposite direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Yama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.14,0:10:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.51,0:10:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after that, Conan decided to play hero and chase after him all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't after him. I had an idea where Mitsuhiko might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sure he would be somewhere near this stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.57,0:10:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something special near the stream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that a treasure's around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. It's because—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.33,0:10:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was right about him being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.75,0:10:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that won't help us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.75,0:10:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.59,0:10:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the cap I borrowed from Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} at the soccer game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:11:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This indicates he was unable to pick it up after dropping it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't think that Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran into the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, we must find him quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may be using the boy as a hostage right now, so make sure everyone is extremely careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.70,0:11:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is running around all over the place, where should we start looking for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's not very far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.75,0:11:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sweat on the cap isn't dry yet and it's still warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, he would have heard you yell his name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't he answer you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.60,0:11:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably lost his voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko most likely came here before noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.23,0:11:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time we finally found our way here, the sun was already setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.19,0:11:57.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Mitsuhiko was yelling for help the whole time because he was lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:12:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, his voice must be a hoarse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.03,0:12:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.99,0:12:08.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with the Detective Badge, he could whisper...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If he answered his Detective Badge, I would have found him easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only he could use his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he hurt his hands or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.43,0:12:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.59,0:12:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time to worry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.10,0:12:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he's around this area, we need to hurry and start looking for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} can't talk, and the serial killer might have found him by now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.27,0:12:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are we going to find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.03,0:12:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's focus on looking for the criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.03,0:12:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't see his face clearly since it was dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.37,0:12:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are we going to tell that guy apart from the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True. According to the news, Numabuchi had...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thin eyebrows, deep-set eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hollow cheeks, upturned nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.80,0:13:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His face looks like a skull with skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.39,0:13:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a beast-like hunchback who moves lightly and has very quick reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we look for someone who looks like a skeleton?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.43,0:13:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds right to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.73,0:13:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how do you know so much about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could Numabuchi be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.99,0:13:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi Kiichiro is a former member of the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.16,0:13:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An ex-member of the "men in black", as you call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.05,0:13:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But alas, he wasn't very important to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.72,0:13:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The syndicate wanted to make him one of their killers because he had the physical qualities and prowess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.60,0:13:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was useless for them after all, so they sent him to my department.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.23,0:13:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to test APTX4869 on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:13:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.11,0:14:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I know so much about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before testing the drug...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.74,0:14:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I received a huge report filled with his stats on his physical and mental abilities, along with his profile picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, he escaped before he came to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And shortly after that, I escaped as well, so I never met him in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ran away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.59,0:14:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he became afraid of the immense power and size of the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.72,0:14:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he ran away... doomed to live in continuous fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have mistaken those three people for pursuers and killed them in panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.23,0:14:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems so pitiful, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.06,0:14:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he killed people for fun before he even joined the Organization, so no one should really pity him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was caught, he shouted "It's all their fault!" at the TV camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. His statement was considered a feeble excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, he wasn't a significant member of the Organization, so they left him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.30,0:15:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you were able to smell the members of the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.22,0:15:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, that's why I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.43,0:15:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't sense anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.44,0:15:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister was able to catch their scent, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.48,0:15:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always relied on that ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I've grown accustomed to living this peaceful life with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.62,0:15:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess my own foolishness will become the end of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means you're finally being able to live a normal life, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.67,0:15:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's not waste any time and continue looking for Mitsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.64,0:15:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he's a crazy guy who wants to see you and Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.73,0:16:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the reason why he came here was—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the beeping of his Detective Badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.08,0:16:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's getting louder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.33,0:16:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's coming closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Mitsuhiko—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Numabuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.68,0:16:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nu-Nu—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.93,0:16:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi Kiichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.68,0:16:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-There he is! I found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put those lights away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're scared of the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:48.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They won't be able to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.53,0:16:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"They"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.95,0:16:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have friends in this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hundreds of them, so beware.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.62,0:16:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think we'll fall for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gosh, we were so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.63,0:17:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.17,0:17:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, your voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your badge was beeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.30,0:17:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why didn't you answer our calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.39,0:17:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.26,0:17:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Are you injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.27,0:17:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.07,0:17:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A firefly?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup. It's a symbol of summer that you can't find in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.03,0:17:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The angry old men that Mitsuhiko was with at the bus stop were probably just environmentalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.16,0:17:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They come to this forest on Sundays and do their best to protect the fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.38,0:17:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko kept asking where the fireflies were, so they got mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:52.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't want a kid messing around in the forest that they work so hard to protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fireflies only live near clear streams and rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.81,0:18:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mitsuhiko really wanted to find them, so he followed one of those men here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.69,0:18:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.82,0:18:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he was staring straight ahead and hiding on the bus...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because he didn't want to lose them or let them know they were being followed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.74,0:18:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And at the bus station, he subconsciously pressed the same button on the ticket machine as they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.00,0:18:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he got an adult ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what does any of this have to do with the names of two warlords?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember what the girl from the flower shop said?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.68,0:18:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said it was "Uesugi and Takeda" or "Toyotomi and Tokugawa."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.01,0:18:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both of those sets of names are pairs of rival warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another famous pair that almost everyone knows is Genji and Heike.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this case, he was referring to the Genji and Heike species of fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about the sasa-dango?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.74,0:18:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was planning to lay their bamboo leaves at the bottom of an insect cage, thus making a firefly habitat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.37,0:19:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, he was going to catch some fireflies and take them home in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.25,0:19:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time Mitsuhiko managed to catch a firefly, he had gone too far into the forest, and was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though he heard the Badge beeping, he couldn't get to it without letting go of his prized firefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.19,0:19:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.90,0:19:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, if you wanted to go bug hunting, you could've invited us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.45,0:19:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dummy. It wouldn't be a surprise if he told everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.41,0:19:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way home from the fireworks, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Haibara said, "I'd love to see fireflies just once!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? So, Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.08,0:19:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did all that just for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.17,0:19:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.63,0:19:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.85,0:20:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why Numabuchi brought Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} here, knowing it would lead to his arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe because they came here for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.69,0:20:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.95,0:20:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was listening to our conversation while he was up in the tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could easily guess that a child came here looking for fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He became sure of it after he saw Mitsuhiko's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.61,0:20:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the story of the fourth body buried here was a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably just wanted to see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.12,0:21:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sight that lit up his heart with immeasurable joy when he played here as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.17,0:22:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.63,0:22:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, did you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.22,0:22:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The news on TV yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.39,0:22:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It said there was an unbelievable discovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.85,0:22:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Did they find Tokugawa's buried treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! They found the legendary animal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.60,0:22:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.11,0:23:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what was it called again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.44,0:23:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't Takenoko, or Kananoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.74,0:23:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchinoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that! They went on to the next topic before I could see what kind of animal it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.00,0:23:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, don't you want to see it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.25,0:23:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.17,0:23:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuchinoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.88,0:23:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, they were also found in the Gifu, Okayama, and Hyogo Prefectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.18,0:23:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah! I'll be visiting my uncle who lives in Gifu soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.77,0:23:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you planning on finding it yourself just to show off?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.69,0:23:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.69,0:23:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.82,0:23:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we go again...
